Augmentation Evoker Mythic+ Guide

11.1 - Undermine(d)

Last Updated:February 25, 2025|Changelog|FAQ

Welcome to the Augmentation Evoker Mythic+ guide for the World of Warcraft patch 11.1! This guide covers everything you need to know to understand your character! Are you starting out and leveling up from 70? Check out the leveling guide!

Hero Talents

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker
  • For most scenarios
    ‍Scalecommander     edges out
    ‍Chronowarden     but both are at a similar power level and whichever is better depends on which buff targets are available.
  • If you have allies with 1.5-minute cooldown timings
    ‍Scalecommander     is superior
  • With 2-minute cooldown timings
    ‍Chronowarden     can be better with current tuning.
‍Chronowarden
‍Scalecommander
  • ‍Temporal Burst     turns
    ‍Tip the Scales     into a strong offensive cooldown that increases your Haste and cooldown recovery rate.
    • The increased Haste, movement Speed and cooldown recovery rate buff effect is reduced by 1% every second during the 30s duration of
      ‍Temporal Burst      .
    • The total reduced cooldown of your abilities is 4.65 seconds.
  • ‍Warp     transforms your normal
    ‍Hover     into a Blink
    • Be cautious as this has a small delay.
    • This currently only works when you are on or close to solid ground, if you are too high up in the air it will become a normal
      ‍Hover      .
  • Similar to your Mastery
    ‍Threads of Fate     causes your Empowered spells to provide an additional damage buff.
    • This ability follows the same Targeting Priority as
      ‍Shifting Sands      .
  • When timed correctly
    ‍Temporality     can be very strong as a minor defensive cooldown whenever you are out of everything else.
  • ‍Golden Opportunity
    • This effect has now become chance based which complicates maximizing your output.
  • ‍Mass Eruption
    • ‍Fire Breath       and
      ‍Upheaval       changes your next
      ‍Eruption       into a
      ‍Mass Eruption       that either strikes up to 3 targets or deals increased damage for each target less than 3.
    • ‍Mass Eruption       can stack up to 2 which means you can cast both empower abilities back to back.
  • ‍Bombardments     Is the major interaction of
    ‍Scalecommander    .
    • ‍Bombardments       does not pandemic which allows you to cast two
      ‍Mass Eruptions       in a row without losing debuff uptime.
    • This also maximizes
      ‍Wingleader       and allows you to make
      ‍Breath of Eons       a 1.5 minute cooldown when optimized.
    • ‍Diverted Power       significantly increases the uptime of
      ‍Momentum Shift      .
  • ‍Hardened Scales     and
    ‍Nimble Flyer     are both extremely effective defensive options and such should almost always be taken.
  • ‍Slipstream     currently restores both charges of your
    ‍Hover     if
    ‍Aerial Mastery     is talented.
    • This can be extremely useful in certain fights if additional
      ‍Hover       uptime is needed.
  • ‍Maneuverability
    • Causes your
      ‍Breath of Eons       to always be aimed in front of your character and can now be steered.
    • This also makes
      ‍Breath of Eons       fly the entire duration unless you cancel it early by pressing the ability once more.
    • Be careful to not spam your
      ‍Breath of Eons       keybind as you might cancel it before it hits your target while still going on cooldown.

Talents

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker
‍Chronowarden
‍Scalecommander

When to use this Spec

Both specs are competitive in organized high, as well as low to mid Mythic+ keys. Use this spec when you play with buff targets that have 2-minute cooldown timings.

Gameplay Altering Talents

Discover all talents that significantly alter your gameplay within the Spec and Class Talent trees. This section gives a concise overview of these talents and their applications but for a more detailed look check out the Rotation and Deep Dive sections below.

Spec Tree

  • ‍Ebon Might
    • Your gameplay as an Augmentation Evoker revolves around optimizing and extending this buff.
  • ‍Prescience
    • This causes the target to become the first priority for your
      ‍Ebon Might       and
      ‍Shifting Sands      .
    • ‍Anachronism       causes
      ‍Prescience       to have a 35% chance of generating one
      ‍Essence Burst      .
  • ‍Breath of Eons
    • Used as your major offensive cooldown in combination with
      ‍Ebon Might       and
      ‍Prescience      .
  • ‍Essence Burst
    • Causes
      ‍Eruption       to apply
      ‍Momentum Shift      .
  • ‍Imminent Destruction
    • ‍Breath of Eons       now reduces
      ‍Eruption       essence cost to 1.
    • With
      ‍Plot the Future       you also gain
      ‍Fury of the Aspects       for 15 seconds.
  • ‍Motes of Possibility
    • ‍Eruption       has a 25% chance to form a mote, allies that come in contact with said mote gain a buff listed below.
    • ‍Symbiotic Bloom
    • ‍Inferno's Blessing
    • ‍Shifting Sands

Class Tree

  • ‍Rescue
    • Use to save your friends by moving them or utilizing
      ‍Twin Guardian      .
    • Optionally, use it as your own personal defensive in certain fights.
  • ‍Zephyr
    • Used to reduce AOE damage across the entire party.
  • ‍Tip the Scales
    • Used to activate
      ‍Temporal Burst
    • Used generally with
      ‍Fire Breath
  • ‍Source of Magic
    • ‍Potent Mana       buffs a friendly healer.
  • ‍Oppressing Roar
    • Combine this with either
      ‍Terror of the Skies       or a friendly CC like
      ‍Sigil of Silence      .
  • ‍Cauterizing Flame
    • Massive for certain encounters, often utilized as a bleed dispel for tank mechanics.

Hero Talents

  • ‍Temporality
    • Since this functions as an extra defensive, it is fully locked in.
  • ‍Double-time
    • Outperforms and is easier to play than
      ‍Time Convergence      .
  • ‍Instability Matrix
    • Outperforms
      ‍Master of Destiny      .

When to use this Spec

Both specs are competitive in organized high, as well as low to mid Mythic+ keys. Use this spec when you play with buff targets that have 45-second or 1.5-minute cooldown timings.

Deep dive

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker

‍Upheaval and
‍Essence Burst

  • Not wasting
    ‍Essence Bursts     is important.
    • With both
      ‍Rockfall       and the 4-set bonus you have
      • 30% chance to gain two
        ‍Essence Burst        .
      • 80% chance to gain one
        ‍Essence Burst        .
    • Considering the above you want to make sure to ideally have 0
      ‍Essence Burst       up at the point of casting
      ‍Upheaval      .

‍Rescue

  • ‍Rescue     is a great part of your toolkit as an Evoker. Using it optimally requires fight awareness, but it can often save your less mobile allies from sticky situations.
  • When you don't need
    ‍Rescue     for its movement part, you should be looking to use it for the very potent defensive effect
    ‍Twin Guardian     as often as possible.

‍Hover

  • Managing and timing your
    ‍Hover     casts correctly in combat to get more casts in while dealing with mechanics is where you see the biggest difference in your DPS. Optimizing your rotation is not that complex for Augmentation Evoker.
  • Starting a cast of a spell such as
    ‍Eruption     at the very end of a
    ‍Hover     buff still lets you finish that specific cast while moving. Keep this in mind to get more benefit from each use of
    ‍Hover    !
  • Make sure you are tracking your uptime and charges of
    ‍Hover     on your UI. Get really comfortable with utilizing this ability as it is the most significant unique strength of an Evoker.

Affixes

The Affix system got revamped going into The War Within Season 1 retiring most Affixes as well as introducing new kiss-curse ones while also changing on which key level these appear.

  • +4 Affixes -- Rotates on a weekly basis
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Pulsar
  • +7 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis
    • ‍Tyrannical
    • ‍Fortified
  • +10 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis, is always the opposite of the +4 Affix
    • ‍Tyrannical
    • ‍Fortified
  • +12 Affix
    • ‍Xal'atath's Guile       -- Replaces the +4 Affix

Following you get some useful tips for handling different Mythic+ Affixes as a Augmentation Evoker.

  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • ‍Tail Swipe       and
      ‍Wing Buffet
    • Be careful to not carelessly pushback the mob pack you are currently fighting.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • Make sure to target the Void Emissary and kill it
    • If needed you can talent into
      ‍Unravel       for this affix.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • Utilize
      ‍Hover       and intercept as many orbs as possible.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
    • You can dispel it with
      ‍Expunge       and
      ‍Cauterizing Flame      .

Stat Priority

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker

Understand your secondary stat priority and the tertiary stats needed for optimal performance during Mythic+ dungeons as a Augmentation Evoker. For more detailed information, visit the Stats and Attributes guide.

‍Chronowarden
‍Scalecommander
  • Aim towards roughly 18-20% Haste.

Higher Item level items are better in most scenarios. Generally you can find stat weights in the Evoker Augmentation discord. In the BiS gear there is more haste than technically optimal according to sims, but having more haste smoothens out the spec and makes it simpler to play.

All secondary stats are affected by diminishing returns. Click here to learn more!

Tertiary

  • Avoidance - Great stat to reduce the damage intake of "Area of Effect" abilities.
  • Leech - Provides additional healing through damage dealing. Most of your damage comes from buffed players, thus it becomes not optimal.
  • Speed - Niche tertiary that can be very useful and has been proven useful in the past. Makes playing certain mechanics a lot easier.

Remaining Sparks

  • Crafted items are 675 item level and regular items are 678 at max item level, therefore it is not beneficial to equip crafted items outside of your 2x embellishments unless you don't have access to other high item level gear on that slot.

Simcraft

To find the best combination of gear available to you or identify the best possible upgrades, visit our Simcraft guide to learn how to utilize Simcraft easily and effectively.

Augmentation Evoker is now technically supported on Raidbots, but they are very early alpha, and you are going to most likely get weird results.

  • If you end up having issues with the simulations and have questions I might not be able to help, for such issues, you could need to ask in the Evoker Discord.
  • DO NOT use Stat Weights Sims, they only affect your personal damage. As such, you won't be given relevant results.
  • Use only Top Gear and Droptimizer.
  • RDPS or "Raid DPS" is the damage dealt by your entire group. This is done because Augmentation is a Support that buffs other DPS therefore they are required for it to operate. Due to this and a few factors mentioned below, sims do not output the contribution of the Augmentation Evoker individually and can only provide comparisons. Thankfully, comparisons are all you need to optimize gear or talent choices.

Log Review

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker
  • With pre-patch, roughly 50-55% of your damage as Augmentation is strictly from your buffs. Due to that, it is vital to buff the correct targets. For the easiest time, you look at Details and buff the top 4 players. The next stage is utilizing Warcraftlogs and buffing the top 4 DPS. For the last stage, you manually input your timings into Warcraftlogs and make decisions upon that.
  • This Section is a WIP and will be continuously updated.

Mouseover Macros

‍Prescience -- Uses
‍Prescience on your mouseover or your target.

#showtooltip Prescience
/cast [@mouseover,help,nodead][] Prescience

‍Cauterizing Flame -- Uses
‍Cauterizing Flame on your mouseover or your target.

#showtooltip Cauterizing Flame(Red)
/cast [@mouseover,help,nodead][] Cauterizing Flame(Red)

‍Time Spiral and
‍Spatial Paradox -- Uses
‍Time Spiral or
‍Spatial Paradox on your mouseover. 

#showtooltip
/cast [known:374968] Time Spiral; [@mouseover] Spatial Paradox

‍Sleep Walk -- Casts
‍Sleep Walk on your mouseover target if it exists. 

#showtooltip
/cast [@mouseover,harm,nodead,exists] Sleep Walk; [harm,nodead] Sleep Walk

Generic and Cancelaura macros

‍Black Attunement -- Removes the need for manually casting
‍Black Attunement and if playing
‍Scalecommander allows you to cancel
‍Breath of Eons early.

#showtooltip Eruption
/cast [nostance:1] Black Attunement
/cancelaura Breath of Eons
/cast Eruption

‍Tip the Scales Cancelaura -- Casts
‍Tip the Scales on first press and cancels the buff on second press.

/cancelaura Tip the Scales(Bronze)
/cast Tip the Scales(Bronze)

Utility Macros

‍Rescue Mouseover -- Casts
‍Rescue on your focus target with the end position being your cursor.

#showtooltip Rescue
/tar [@focus]
/cast [@cursor] Rescue
/targetlasttarget

‍Rescue Mouseover -- Casts
‍Rescue on your target with the end position being your cursor.

#showtooltip 
/cast [@cursor] Rescue

Addons

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker

Below, you see a screenshot of the author's User Interface for their Augmentation Evoker, outlining which addons are used and how they are utilized in Mythic+ dungeons to make your life easier.

Addons

  • ElvUI -- Full User Interface replacement
    • A user interface designed around user-friendliness with extra features that are not included in the standard UI.
    • Alternatively, you can also use Shadowed Unit Frames (SUF) and an action bar addon of your choice or of course the stock UI.
  • LittleWigs -- Generic Boss Mod
    • BigWigs is a boss encounter add-on. It consists of many individual encounter scripts, or boss modules; mini add-ons that are designed to trigger alert messages, timer bars, sounds, and so forth, for one specific Raid encounter.
  • WeakAuras -- Jack of all trades
    • WeakAuras is a powerful and flexible framework that allows the display of highly customizable graphics on World of Warcraft's user interface to indicate buffs, debuffs, and other relevant information. This addon was created to be a lightweight replacement for Power Auras but has since introduced more functionalities while remaining efficient and easy to use.
  • Plater -- Advanced Nameplates
    • Plater is a nameplate addon with an extraordinary amount of settings, out of the box debuff tracking, threat coloring, and support for scripting similar to WeakAuras and wago.io + the WeakAuras-Companion for Mod/Script/Profile updates.
  • Details -- In-depth Damage Meter
    • Most powerful, reliable, handsome, damage meter.
  • OmniCD -- Party track addon
    • Helpful addon for Mythic+ to check the available cooldowns of your party.

WeakAuras

Spell CDs on Nameplate by Meeres

This aura shows you the cooldown of spells next to their nameplate.

Ebon Might "Punch" by Xephyris

Plays a sound when casting

‍Eruption,
‍Fire Breath or
‍Upheaval. without
‍Ebon Might up or if it will expire before cast success.

Changes this Patch

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Augmentation Evoker

Patch 11.1

  • ‍Evoker
    • ‍Rescue       now clears movement impairing effects from you and your target.
    • ‍Sleep Walk       now has a 1.7 second cast time (was 1.5 seconds).
  • ‍Augmentation
    • New Talent:
      ‍Rockfall       –
      ‍Upheaval       reaches maximum empower level 20% faster and has a 60% chance to grant
      ‍Essence Burst      .
    • Close as Clutchmates has been re-added –
      ‍Ebon Might       and
      ‍Breath of Eons       are now 10% more effective outside of raid.
    • ‍Ebon Might       no longer applies to tanks and healers.
    • ‍Motes of Possibility       chance to trigger increased to 25% (was 15%).
    • ‍Rumbling Earth       deals 30% of
      ‍Upheavals       damage (was 50%).
    • ‍Breath of Eons       now accumulates 8% of damage taken (was 10%).
    • ‍Shifting Sands       Versatility effectiveness reduced by 20%.
    • While in dungeons and raids, allies can no longer see additional
      ‍Upheavals       from
      ‍Rumbling Earth      .
    • ‍Seismic Slam       talent has moved to PvP talents.

Patch 11.0.5

  • ‍Evoker
    • ‍Tail Swipe       is now learned baseline for Evokers.
    • ‍Permeating Chill       is now baseline for Evoker.
    • ‍Unravel       damage increased by 25%.
    • ‍Blessing of the Bronze       now costs 1% base mana (was 4%).
    • ‍Clobbering Sweep       reduces
      ‍Tail Swipe      ’s cooldown by 2 minutes (was 45 seconds).
    • ‍Heavy Wingbeats       reduces
      ‍Wing Buffet      ’s cooldown by 2 minutes (was 45 seconds).
    • ‍Renewing Blaze       is no longer affected by healing received modifiers (both positive and negative). Dampening in arena is a special case and will continue to decrease the healing of Renewing Blaze.
    • ‍Heavy Wingbeats       and
      ‍Clobbering Sweep       are no longer a choice node, and their position has changed in the class tree.
    • ‍Permeating Chill       no longer spams immune messages when attacking enemies who are immune to slows
  • ‍Augmentation
    • ‍Imminent Destruction
      ‍Breath of Eons       reduces the essence cost of
      ‍Eruption       by 1 and increases its damage by 10% for 15 sec (was 12 seconds) after you land.
    • ‍Molten Embers
      ‍Fire Breath       causes enemies to take up to 40% (was 20%) increased damage from your Black spells, increased based on its empower level.

Patch 11.0.2

  • ‍Evoker
    • ‍Disintegrate       damage increased by 10%.
    • ‍Fire Breath       damage increased by 10%.
    • ‍Azure Strike       damage increased by 10%.
    • ‍Deep Breath       damage increased by 10%.
    • ‍Verdant Embrace       healing increased by 20%.
    • ‍Living Flame       healing increased by 30%.
  • ‍Augmentation
    • ‍Black Attunement       increases the maximum health of you and 4 nearby allies by 2% (was 4%).
    • ‍Aspects' Favor       increases Black Attunement by 1% max health per talent point invested (was 2%).
    • ‍Ebon Might       increases primary stat by 5% (was 6.5%).
    • ‍Close as Clutchmates       has been removed.

Patch 11.0

  • ‍Evoker
    • All talent trees have had many talents move locations or have had their pathing updated. 
    • Evokers now start at level 10 (was level 58) and the one-Evoker-per-realm restriction has been removed.
    • Evokers now unlock the talent pane immediately after choosing a specialization in the Forbidden Reach, and they no longer learn “temporary” talents as they complete the Forbidden Reach experience.
    • Several base spells that were previously learned at level 58 are now learned at level 10.
    • ‍Mass Return       is now learned at level 38 (was level 59).
    • ‍Fury of the Aspects       is now learned at level 48 (was level 60).
    • ‍Overawe       has been redesigned – Now grants 30 seconds of cooldown reduction (was cooldown reduction per Enrage dispelled).
    • ‍Spatial Paradox       has moved to the Class tree (was Augmentation) and its cooldown increased to 3 minutes (was 2 minutes). Choice node with
      ‍Time Spiral      .
    • ‍Lifecinders       now upgrades
      ‍Renewing Blaze       to allow 1 friendly target. If no target is selected, it will find a nearby injured ally.
    • ‍Panacea       healing reduced by 50% and now also heals the caster when
      ‍Verdant Embrace       is cast. 
    • ‍Panacea       is now considered a Green spell, and is improved by Lush Growth.
    • ‍Oppressing Roar       cone radius increased to 60 degrees (was 45 degrees).
    • ‍Landslide       now roots targets for 15 seconds (was 30 seconds)
  • ‍Augmentation
    • New Talent:
      ‍Arcane Reach       – The range of your helpful magics is increased by 5 yards.
    • New Passive:
      ‍Sense Power       – While enabled, allies with their major cooldown active will be highlighted in the game field and will display a buff icon on party and raid frames. Learned automatically and can be toggled on/off.
    • New Talent:
      ‍Rumbling Earth       –
      ‍Upheaval       causes an aftershock at its location, dealing 50% of its damage 2 additional times.
    • New Talent:
      ‍Molten Embers       –
      ‍Fire Breath       causes enemies to take 20% more damage from your Black spells.
    • New Talent:
      ‍Imminent Destruction       –
      ‍Breath of Eons       reduces the Essence cost of Eruption by 1 and increases its damage by 10% for 12 seconds after you land.
    • ‍Prescience       has been updated – When cast without a friendly target, the smart-targeting will now prefer damage role players who have their major cooldowns active.
    • ‍Spatial Paradox       has moved to the Class tree.
    • ‍Motes of Possibility       now give a random Augmentation Evoker buff (was reduces the cooldown of your major ability by 10 seconds). In addition, the motes will spawn closer to the caster, and they will also slowly float towards the nearest ally.
    • ‍Overlord       now guarantees
      ‍Motes of Possibility       will spawn from the Eruptions it casts.
    • ‍Echoing Strike       now also increase
      ‍Azure Strike       damage by 15%.
    • ‍Reactive Hide       increases damage of
      ‍Blistering Scales       by 15% per stack (was 10%).
    • The following talents are now 1 point:
      • ‍Seismic Slam         is now a 1-point talent. The stun duration remains at 4 seconds.
    • The following talents have been removed:
      • ‍Geomancy         has been removed.

Q: Do you play around
‍Momentum Shift?

Yes, you want to attempt to snipe gaining

‍Essence Bursts for
‍Momentum Shift as more often than not you don't lose anything by attempting to do so.

F.e. If you end up with 2x

‍Essence Burst and 6 essence you want to

  • Cast
    ‍Eruption     with
    ‍Essence Burst
  • Cast
    ‍Eruption     with
    ‍Essence Burst
  • Cast
    ‍Eruption
    Cast
    ‍Living Flame     attempting to snipe an
    ‍Essence Burst     for a
    ‍Momentum Shift     extension
